---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import AudioPlayer from '../components/AudioPlayer.astro';

const title = "Related Links - ParrotSpeech.org";
const description = "Links to studies of animals using human language, experiments with interspecies communication, and parrot-related sites.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navigation slot="navigation" currentPage="links" />
  
  <article>
    <Breadcrumb currentPage="Related Links" />

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Related Links</h1>
      <div class="header-image">
        <img src="/images/Come_on_pick_me_up.jpg" alt="Arielle the macaw" />
        <span class="photo-credit">Photo by Linda Carpenter</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Audio Feature Section -->
    <section class="audio-feature">
      <div class="audio-box">
        <div class="transcription-box">
          <p>Arielle said,<br/>"I want out!"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audio-content">
          <p class="audio-description">
            Arielle can be a demanding bird.<br/>
            She says what one might expect<br/>
            from a bird in this position, click<br/>
            the play button to hear her speak.
          </p>
          <AudioPlayer src="/media/Track_CC.wav" title="Arielle: I want out!" />
          <p class="audio-note">The transcription is in the yellow box below.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Heading -->
    <section class="main-intro">
      <h2 class="fancy-heading">With a little help from her friends</h2>
      <p class="intro-text">
        The following links lead to studies of "animals using human language," experiments with interspecies 
        communication, and parrot-related sites.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Links About Apes -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>Link About Apes</h3>
      <p>
        This link takes you to the site for the language-using gorilla, Koko at 
        <a href="http://www.gorilla.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Gorilla Foundation</a>
        <span class="url-display">• www.gorilla.org</span>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Links About Whales & Dolphins -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>Link About Whales & Dolphins</h3>
      <p>
        This site is mainly about cetaceans, but it also deals with a variety of subjects related to interspecies 
        communication. [Interspecies Inc., Friday Harbor, WA] Go to 
        <a href="http://www.interspecies.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the interspecies site</a>
        <span class="url-display">www.interspecies.com</span>
      </p>
      <p class="article-reference">
        Article about Arielle:<br/>
        Knollman, James. "Slow Dreaming." <em>Interspecies</em>, Winter 2004.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Links About Keeping & Training Pet Birds -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>Links About Keeping & Training Pet Birds</h3>
      <p>
        <a href="http://www.afabirds.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Federation of Aviculture</a>
        <span class="url-display">• www.afabirds.org</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        An extensive web site with information about parrots including the owner's Grey parrot, Kibibi, is at 
        <a href="http://www.infosuperflyway.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.infosuperflyway.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        My article "Recording Speech by Birds" is found on the Kibibi site at<br/>
        <a href="http://www.infosuperflyway.com/articles/recording-birds.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          http://www.infosuperflyway.com/articles/recording-birds.php
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Another site about parrots is imabird.com. You can check out information about my book, 
        <em>Another Kind of Mind: A Talking Bird Masters English</em>, on Barry's web site at 
        <a href="http://www.imabird.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.imabird.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Pet Guardian Angels of America -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>Pet Guardian Angels of America</h3>
      <p>
        <a href="http://www.pgaa.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PGAA</a> (www.pgaa.com) is an animal rescue organization. The 
        PGAA site features a couple of my articles below.
      </p>
      <ul class="article-list">
        <li>
          Article 1: "Recording Speech by Birds"<br/>
          <a href="http://www.pgaa.com/avain/general/daltonrecordingbirds.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            http://www.pgaa.com/avain/general/daltonrecordingbirds.html
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Article 2: "Talking Birds, Intelligent Creatures"<br/>
          <a href="http://www.pgaa.com/avain/general/daltontalkingbird.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            http://www.pgaa.com/avain/general/daltontalkingbird.html
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Local Bird Clubs -->
    <section class="link-category info-box">
      <p>
        Don't overlook local bird clubs for information. Check your local newspaper for 
        information. If the clubs are not printed regularly, you might try a telephone call 
        to the clubs editor for the most up-to-date information. You can search on the Internet too.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're interested in companion birds, including parrots and other talking birds, use 
        the links above as a starting point. If you know of a related link that is not included 
        here, feel free to suggest additions by e-mail.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Links About Writing -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>Links About Writing</h3>
      <p>
        The author is a member of a writers' group in Florida. If you are interested in writing or wish to explore 
        interests related to the group, it is called PINAWOR (Pinellas Authors and Writers Organization Inc.). For 
        more information visit their web site at: 
        <a href="http://www.pinawor.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">• www.pinawor.org</a>
      </p>

      <div class="writer-friend">
        <h4>My Parrot Writer Friend</h4>
        <div class="writer-content">
          <img src="/images/clip_image002.jpg" alt="Parrot writer friend" class="writer-image" />
          <p>
            Two Parrot Stories, a children's picture book (age 6 and up), or in 
            reading articles about parrots in history, or about speech and body 
            language, please visit the author's website at
            <a href="http://www.rosemarieriechelbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.rosemarieriechelbooks.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TV Links About Arielle -->
    <section class="link-category">
      <h3>TV Links About Arielle</h3>
      
      <div class="media-item">
        <h4>Humorous interview</h4>
        <p class="small-url">http://www.studio10.tv/category/authors/segment.aspx/84258/Another_Kind_of_Mind</p>
        <a href="/videos/WTSP_July2008.mp4" class="video-link">Click here to see video clip</a>
      </div>

      <div class="media-item">
        <h4>Interview about speech research/cognitive speech</h4>
        <p>The most recent clip from WTVT-13, Tampa — 29 September 2010</p>
        <a href="/videos/Fox13_News_Animal_Talk_1.mp4" class="video-link">Arielle on TV ... Hear Her Speak</a>
      </div>

      <div class="media-item">
        <p class="radio-intro">
          Radio host John Austin and the author discuss the book <em>ANOTHER KIND OF MIND: A Talking Bird Masters English</em>
        </p>
        <a href="http://www.internetradiopros.com/bookclub/?p=episode&name=2012-10-18_zbookclub_for_102312_2nd_segment_michael_dalton.mp3" 
           target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="radio-link">
          Listen to the radio interview
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ParrotSpeech Group -->
    <section class="parrotspeech-group">
      <p class="group-intro">
        If you are interested in speech by talking birds, below are the details about the ParrotSpeech Group:
      </p>
      
      <h3>Description</h3>
      <p>
        People interested in the study of spontaneous speech by talking birds. The topics of 
        concern include learning theory, speech recognition, recording speech, cognitive 
        speech by talking birds, linguistics, conversations with parrot-like birds, cognition, 
        consciousness, and other topics related to the talking birds. To join click on the 
        subscription link or paste the following link into your browser:
      </p>
      <p class="subscribe-email">
        <a href="mailto:ParrotSpeech-subscribe@yahoogroups.com">ParrotSpeech-subscribe@yahoogroups.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer Quote -->
    <section class="footer-quote">
      <p>
        Arielle understands speech and speaks thoughtfully using English words, phrases, and sentences.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    color: #663300;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .header-image {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .header-image img {
    max-width: 530px;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .photo-credit {
    display: block;
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #cccccc;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* Audio Feature Section */
  .audio-feature {
    margin: 30px 0;
  }

  .audio-box {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    background: #ffff00;
    padding: 15px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .transcription-box {
    background: #ffff00;
    padding: 15px;
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 120px;
  }

  .transcription-box p {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .audio-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .audio-description {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .audio-note {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  /* Main Intro */
  .main-intro {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .fancy-heading {
    font-family: 'Comic Sans MS', cursive, sans-serif;
    color: #000099;
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .intro-text {
    color: #663300;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Link Categories */
  .link-category {
    margin: 30px 0;
    padding: 20px;
    background: #f9f9f9;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #663300;
  }

  .link-category h3 {
    font-family: 'Comic Sans MS', cursive, sans-serif;
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .link-category p {
    color: #663300;
    font-weight: bold;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .link-category a {
    color: #0000ff;
  }

  .link-category a:visited {
    color: #800080;
  }

  .url-display {
    margin-left: 20px;
    color: #663300;
  }

  .article-reference {
    margin-top: 15px;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .article-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 15px 0;
  }

  .article-list li {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .info-box {
    background: #fff;
    border-left-color: #009966;
  }

  /* Writer Friend Section */
  .writer-friend {
    margin-top: 25px;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .writer-friend h4 {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .writer-content {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .writer-image {
    width: 127px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .writer-content p {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 250px;
  }

  /* Media Items */
  .media-item {
    margin-bottom: 25px;
    padding-bottom: 20px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .media-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .media-item h4 {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .small-url {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #663300;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  .video-link, .radio-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .radio-intro {
    font-family: 'Comic Sans MS', cursive, sans-serif;
    color: #000066;
  }

  /* ParrotSpeech Group */
  .parrotspeech-group {
    margin: 40px 0;
    padding: 25px;
    background: #f0f8ff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #000099;
  }

  .parrotspeech-group .group-intro {
    color: #000099;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .parrotspeech-group h3 {
    font-family: 'Comic Sans MS', cursive, sans-serif;
    color: #000099;
    text-decoration: underline;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .parrotspeech-group p {
    color: #000099;
    font-weight: bold;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .subscribe-email {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .subscribe-email a {
    color: #000099;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Footer Quote */
  .footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 40px 0;
    padding: 25px;
  }

  .footer-quote p {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .audio-box {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .writer-content {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .fancy-heading {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
